
[1]inwardly

   IN'WARDLY, adv. In the inner parts; internally.

   Let Benedict, like covered fire,

   Consume away in sighs, waste inwardly.

   1. In the heart; privately; secretly. He inwardly repines. It is not
   easy to treat with respect a person whom we inwardly despise.

   2. Towards the center.
